law.catch_line: Submission of implementation plans to board.

text.section: The secretary shall present annually to the board for its review and approval implementation plans for the approved strategies as set forth in the Commonwealth's approved strategic economic development plan for which funds will be expended by the cabinet or other agencies receiving funds from the cabinet.
Any agency receiving funds from or through the cabinet shall submit annually implementation plans to the board for its review and approval.

law.history: Created 1992 Ky. Acts ch. 105, sec. 8, effective July 14, 1992.
